      <item>
        <title>Lo-Fi tips anyone?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[TheRealJFalc]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Turn the lowpass down a lot on the drums. That’s my recommendation.</p>
<p>If you’re looking for some ideas of drum patterns, I used an alteration and a slowed down form of the Amen Break <a href="https://soundcloud.com/james-lucien-official/the-man-who-cares-too-much" rel="nofollow noopener">for my lo-fi song I did a while ago</a>. Then I added some more drums on top of it to give it more of an effect, especially the hi-hats.</p>
<p>I’d also recommend using the electric pianos for basic chords that are lowpassed down to give it more of an atmospheric feel.</p>
          <p><a href="https://disco.auxy.co/t/lo-fi-tips-anyone/7367/5">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
